I think he is one of the best profs i came across at UofT. He took a lot of interest in teaching us and was very adaptable to all kind of questions. Yes he has a similar kind of testing method but prior preparation is must to do well. Recommended 100% not sure tho if he is still teaching.

One of the best profs. NOT because he's easy, but character. Used to work for US government, smart guy but humble about it,doesn't act like it. Funny person and it's not artificial sense of humour; he's just a funny person! He's retiring soon; I suggest you take a course with him before you regret. Highly recommend, no regrets, wish him the best.
horrible Prof. Dont bother going to class.. just rad the text book.
nice prof but hard test
you'll never be able to understand what he writes and draws. carr's hands are as crippled as they get.

He's a really nice guy and puts in a lot of effort into answering questions. However, his notes are not very clear and sometimes  incomplete. He's not the most organized professor, but he still makes Economics really interesting and applies it to everyday life which is kind of refreshing.
Very experienced professor, he got his PhD since 1971, long time, loved how he applied economic concept into real life, interesting to go to his class, one of my best prof in 1st year.

Great prof, able to make dry material interesting. He hums and haws a bit, but is a brilliant professor. Make sure to ask him any questions you have, he is great and will answer all questions he can during lecture. Carr is top notch!!
He is a really good prof, those who only desire a simple introduction to economic should definitely take the course.

Prof Carr was by far my  best professor in first year. If anyone can make economics interesting, accessible, and still manage to take questions in a class of 500 they are a fine prof in my books. Keep it going Jack, You are an AMAZING prof. To those who say he is hard, go to class more often.

the TA is mean, he marks our tests meanly...he likes to give 0 to everybody. carr is friendly and approchable but he doesn't explain clearly. You can hardly understand his lecture if you don't read the textbook although it's hard to read and useless.

Prof Carr was very ineffective. The midterms happen to usually focus on certain chapters-no balance at all. This led to very low marks & bell-curves took place. The final exam was much easier than the 2 midterms. The grading is very heavy -2 midterms: 25% each & final exam: 50%. Definetly keep in mind the course evaluation.I would not recommend him

Although Professor Carr's notes was a little messey, specially during the last five minutes, he explained and communicated very well. His wisdom, knowledge and teaching skills showed every lecture. Also even with the large class, he went out of his way to answer the students questions weather during or after class. So far the best prof I had!

Intelligent, interesting, engaging.  Generally very understandable.  Be warned though: Let's just say he's a little more Stephen Harper than Jack Layton.  "If you love trees use more paper" - that was my favourite.
Explains the best and really enthusiastic. Will answer all your questions
Wonderful instructor! Lectures are clear and interesting...

He is the best ECO100 instructor for those students whose main goal is to gain a broad, conceptual understanding of basic economic principles.  If you're looking for a mathematical approach, Carr will disappoint.  But if you want a really good introduction to economics without any of the equations, he's great.  Plenty of equations in higher years.

Not extremely organized, interesting lectures, not really approachable, but his tests are ok, not hard compare to the other profs. My first test was belled by 18%, but be aware of the 2nd test cuz he doesnt tend to bell the 2nd

Ok, i dont know what the other guy is talking about...  Honestly, Prof. Carr is a fantastic lecturer!  Study his past tests exams and you'll do fine as he repeats many of his questions.  The only thing is that if you go into his class with no or little political knowledge you become a libertarian.  Otherwise, I STRONGLY RECOMMEND HIM!

Absolutely fantastic lecturer.  BEWARE, however, of his tests. They don't test your knowledge of the material; they test your ability to refute ridiculous statements in the precise way he would, and his TAs are not kind. If you're in it for the marks, you should probably go with another prof.

Not bad, not bad. But DOESN'T have an appropriate website with FORUM where students can post their lectures or ask each other questions in order to have a basic communication, moreover no MARKS ONLINE. :(((( It should have every course in UofT by default! I still don't know my marks haha.

Eventhough the prof is very helpful and very easy, somebody has to tell him that this is not the course to impose his capitalistic views to undergrads. He once said "if you want to save trees, use more and more paper". He is obsessed with free trade and capitalistic views. needs to focus on teaching the basics rather than imposing views.
awesome; very clear insights and good examples. doesnt use complicated math but examinations are very hard.
A very enthusiastic/funny lecturer. Tests were fair and very similiar to past years' tests.

Excellent prof!  Uses same funny examples in both courses! :D His TA's can be a **** with marking but u always know what's his "perfect answer."  In ECO 209, always uses "True, False or Uncertain" format where "no marks for T/F/U, all marks for explanation!"  He's predictable & you don't need the textbook...  Just come to class & buy ECOMAN tests!
This prof tests on theory rather than numerical calculations, that might not be good if you intend to continue in economics, but overall his teaching sparked my interest in economics.

Excellent professor. Try to get his section if at all possible. No need to get the text, all you need to know for the test he teaches in class! Also, tests are pretty much the same from year to year, so if you buy (or photocopy) ECOMAN's past tests you'll be fine.

He's a very goof prof! I learned SO much about Economics in his class...I was not excited AT ALL about economics before taking it, but Carr made the class enjoyable, easy to follow, and he really encouraged debate and discussion! CHOOSE HIM!
professor carr is by far the best prof i have ever had. he is passionate and very engaging. you will not fall asleep in his class. his passion for economics is very contagious. amazing prof.

In first year, I thought Carr was a great prof, with good examples, and decent tests...however, although his micro sections were good...his macro section of the year was horrible.  I didn't learn anything, and the third test costed me my first year mark.  His 209 class isn't so great either.

This prof should leave his political bent out of the class. Chances are if you entered the class with no political leanings, you left as a neo-con/libertarian. Also Mr. Carr, if you're trying to prove that world poverty is on the decline, don't use statistics from the World Bank -lol.

He is a good professor... I liked his lectures, although his handwritings were often not clear (as everybody else complain!). But he teaches with actual examples in real world, which is more interesting than just theory.
he's a great prof overall.
he was good in eco100 maybe coz of the help of the screen which made his handwriting legible but...in 209, without that screen i cant read what he writes
